1
00:00:07,241 --> 00:00:08,175
Ging: Hmm?

2
00:00:09,409 --> 00:00:10,677
What do you want?

3
00:00:10,711 --> 00:00:12,546
cheadle: I heard
that you are leaving tomorrow.

4
00:00:12,579 --> 00:00:15,649
Walking away from the election
and your son?

5
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:17,350
Ging: That bald shrimp!

6
00:00:17,384 --> 00:00:20,254
Why did he tell her,
of all people?

7
00:00:20,287 --> 00:00:22,990
Cheadle: Why not stay
and see it through?

8
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:24,992
Ging: We already know
the outcome.

9
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:27,594
I’ve had my fun, so i’m going.

10
00:00:27,628 --> 00:00:30,364
Meeting that leorio guy
was the highlight.

11
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:33,267
He’s got huge potential.
No doubt about that.

12
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,169
Cheadle: What are
you talking about?

13
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:38,205
We’ve got four candidates left.
Nothing’s been decided.

14
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:40,040
Ging: Yeah, exactly.

15
00:00:40,073 --> 00:00:42,175
That is what i’m talking about.

16
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:43,977
Cheadle: Huh?

17
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:45,212
♪

18
00:00:45,245 --> 00:00:47,447
(♪ singing in Japanese )

19
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:17,744
♪ You can smile again

20
00:01:17,778 --> 00:01:20,014
( singing in Japanese )

21
00:01:20,047 --> 00:01:23,684
♪ You can fly away

22
00:01:23,717 --> 00:01:25,652
( singing in Japanese )

23
00:01:31,058 --> 00:01:33,961
♪

24
00:01:35,829 --> 00:01:39,032
Ging: I plan on voting
for you today, cheadle.

25
00:01:39,066 --> 00:01:42,036
Good job. See you.

26
00:01:42,069 --> 00:01:45,039
Cheadle: What in the world
are you saying?

27
00:01:45,072 --> 00:01:46,440
Are you dumb?

28
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:49,743
Ging: I’m saying the outcome
will be no outcome.

29
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:52,646
Wanna know how many days
until this is over?

30
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:55,081
Cheadle: But how
could you know that?

31
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:58,118
Ging: You and mizai are in this
to win. That’s how.

32
00:01:58,151 --> 00:02:00,820
But if you really wanted to win,

33
00:02:00,854 --> 00:02:04,124
then you should have tried
a lot harder before.

34
00:02:05,192 --> 00:02:06,727
You needed to secure a majority

35
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,795
and clear
the turnout requirement.

36
00:02:08,829 --> 00:02:11,265
You should have used
any means necessary

37
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:13,167
in rounds two and three.

38
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,202
Cheadle: Why are you
telling me this?

39
00:02:15,235 --> 00:02:17,237
All that’s easy to say
in hindsight.

40
00:02:17,271 --> 00:02:19,473
Ging: If i’d warned you
about it beforehand,

41
00:02:19,506 --> 00:02:21,141
you’d have done the opposite.

42
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:23,177
Ugh. You’re so difficult.

43
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:26,680
look, feel free
to chalk it up to hindsight.

44
00:02:26,713 --> 00:02:29,683
It won’t make judgment day
come any slower.

45
00:02:29,716 --> 00:02:31,518
Cheadle: Wait! Stop!

46
00:02:31,552 --> 00:02:32,653
Ging: Now what?

47
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:36,089
( Cheadle sighs )

48
00:02:36,123 --> 00:02:38,258
Fine. I’ll do whatever you say.

49
00:02:38,292 --> 00:02:40,127
What’s it going to be?

50
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,629
Ging: It sure doesn’t sound
like you’re too happy about it.

51
00:02:44,731 --> 00:02:47,834
Cheadle: I have no idea
what pariston is thinking.

52
00:02:47,868 --> 00:02:49,169
( Sighs )

53
00:02:49,203 --> 00:02:51,639
So can you tell me
how to beat him?

54
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:53,707
Ging: You’ve never done
anything i’ve said.

55
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:57,577
this seems a bit
out of character for you, but...

56
00:02:57,611 --> 00:03:01,648
All right, fine. We’ll begin
with pariston’s way of thinking.

57
00:03:01,682 --> 00:03:02,750
Listen closely.

58
00:03:04,618 --> 00:03:07,254
He doesn’t want to win,
not really,

59
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:09,289
but he doesn’t want
to lose, either.

60
00:03:09,323 --> 00:03:11,592
That makes him strong.

61
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:13,193
( Cheadle gasps )

62
00:03:13,227 --> 00:03:15,896
Hold on. How can that be?

63
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:17,864
Ging: Yeah, yeah, I know.

64
00:03:17,898 --> 00:03:19,733
Your strong common sense
tells you

65
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:22,769
that your will to win
makes you the stronger one.

66
00:03:22,803 --> 00:03:24,471
I’m right, aren’t I?

67
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:26,907
Nothing wrong with that.
you’re right.

68
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:30,310
and that’s why
you’re so easy to read,

69
00:03:30,344 --> 00:03:33,647
especially when you
want to win a game,

70
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:37,417
and you can’t win this game
unless you have more votes.

71
00:03:37,451 --> 00:03:39,186
Cheadle: A game?

72
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:42,789
Ging: See? You thought I was
just being amoral, didn’t you?

73
00:03:42,823 --> 00:03:45,426
and because you’re
so big on morals, balance,

74
00:03:45,459 --> 00:03:48,329
and doing things by the book,
that ticks you off.

75
00:03:48,362 --> 00:03:49,430
( Cheadle scoffs )

76
00:03:49,463 --> 00:03:51,165
Ging: Hey, look at me!

77
00:03:51,198 --> 00:03:53,734
You’re not acting much like
your dog persona right now.

78
00:03:53,767 --> 00:03:55,335
You’re just being yourself.

79
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:58,539
Pariston’s familiar
with both sides of you,

80
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:01,608
so he knows when you switch
from one to the other.

81
00:04:01,642 --> 00:04:03,777
he knows exactly
what you’re thinking about

82
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:05,745
and what you’ll do next.

83
00:04:05,779 --> 00:04:09,783
It makes you easy to beat,
and he still doesn’t want to.

84
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:10,950
He’s tough, right?

85
00:04:10,984 --> 00:04:13,320
Cheadle: Then what
do you suggest I do?

86
00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:14,554
Ging: I told you already!

87
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:16,757
sure, I could
just tell you what to do,

88
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:19,259
but, if I did,
you’d never listen.

89
00:04:19,293 --> 00:04:21,495
How many times do we
have to go through this?

90
00:04:22,896 --> 00:04:25,232
Okay, i’ll tell you
what’s gonna happen

91
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,967
if the game continues as is.

92
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,969
After the next vote,

93
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:31,571
you and pariston
will be all that’s left.

94
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:33,574
In the two-candidate vote
after that,

95
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:35,676
first and second will flip.

96
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:37,211
( Cheadle gasps )

97
00:04:37,244 --> 00:04:40,380
Ging: That’s gonna happen
every single time.

98
00:04:40,414 --> 00:04:42,650
( Cheadle sighs )

99
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:44,785
Pariston wants
the turnout rate low,

100
00:04:44,818 --> 00:04:47,487
so we can expect
the temp hunters

101
00:04:47,521 --> 00:04:50,591
he has under his thumb
to abstain, all of them.

102
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:51,825
Cheadle: Why’s that?

103
00:04:51,859 --> 00:04:53,427
Ging: Like I said,

104
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:56,296
it’s a game he doesn’t
want to win or lose,

105
00:04:56,330 --> 00:04:58,732
so he’ll drag this out
until the last day.

106
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:02,402
He just wants to have some fun.

107
00:05:02,436 --> 00:05:04,371
He’s just like netero and me.

108
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:07,307
well, except I
get bored a lot faster.

109
00:05:07,341 --> 00:05:09,910
But that guy is patient.

110
00:05:09,943 --> 00:05:11,745
If the vote was about

111
00:05:11,778 --> 00:05:14,347
who’s following
in netero’s footsteps...

112
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:17,318
Pariston’s the winner.

113
00:05:17,351 --> 00:05:18,719
( Cheadle gasps )

114
00:05:18,752 --> 00:05:21,455
Shut up! I don’t want
to hear that from you!

115
00:05:23,757 --> 00:05:25,926
Ging: You’re jealous of him,
aren’t you?

116
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:29,663
what, did you love
that pervy old man that much?

117
00:05:30,964 --> 00:05:32,432
Cheadle: Shut up!

118
00:05:32,466 --> 00:05:33,834
You are so arrogant!

119
00:05:33,867 --> 00:05:36,536
You just have to tell me
when the election will end,

120
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:39,373
you idiot!
So go on! When is it?

121
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:44,044
Ging: Sure, I can do that,
but, before it’s over,

122
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:47,681
learn to stay in character.
You’re impossible to talk to.

123
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:53,320
The day netero blew up,
100 airships

124
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:57,557
belonging to the association
set off for east gorteau.

125
00:05:57,591 --> 00:06:00,661
There’s no record
of their departure.

126
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:03,664
On paper, they’re all
in hangars for maintenance.

127
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:06,733
You didn’t know anything
about that, did you?

128
00:06:06,767 --> 00:06:09,770
you should make friends
with some mechanics and pilots.

129
00:06:09,803 --> 00:06:12,673
Cheadle: What are
you talking about?

130
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:15,709
ging: They recovered
approximately 5,000 cocoons,

131
00:06:15,742 --> 00:06:17,477
half-human, half-beast cocoons

132
00:06:17,511 --> 00:06:19,913
that were made
by the chimera ants.

133
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:24,518
they have
the ability to use nen,

134
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:27,487
and i’d be willing to bet
they’ve hatched by now.

135
00:06:27,521 --> 00:06:30,557
And now that he’s got
such a big playground,

136
00:06:30,591 --> 00:06:33,494
pariston plans to have
a little fun with them.

137
00:06:33,527 --> 00:06:37,931
The day of reckoning will be
the day of the next hunter exam.

138
00:06:37,965 --> 00:06:40,801
however,
if the bylaws are reformed,

139
00:06:40,834 --> 00:06:43,036
the situation might change some.

140
00:06:44,438 --> 00:06:46,540
Figure the rest out yourself.

141
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,041
You’re a hunter, right?

142
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:53,680
- ( Fanfare playing )
- Piyon: All right, everyone!

143
00:06:53,714 --> 00:06:55,716
we will now begin
the eighth round of voting

144
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:58,118
for the election
of the 13th chairman.

145
00:06:58,151 --> 00:07:02,589
Each of the four candidates
will help us kick things off

146
00:07:02,623 --> 00:07:04,625
by reading speeches
they’ve prepared.

147
00:07:04,658 --> 00:07:07,794
After that, we’ll hold
a brief q-and-a session.

148
00:07:07,828 --> 00:07:10,631
Then we’ll move on to the vote.

149
00:07:10,664 --> 00:07:14,034
Leorio: How in the hell
did this happen?

150
00:07:14,067 --> 00:07:17,437
( Sighs )
I guess it’s my fault.

151
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:20,074
piyon: Now, not all
of the candidates qualified,

152
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:21,642
and those that didn’t

153
00:07:21,675 --> 00:07:25,546
will begin with their comments
for the association.

154
00:07:25,579 --> 00:07:28,882
Botobai: I’ll start by thanking
everyone who supported me

155
00:07:28,916 --> 00:07:31,051
in this election.
Thank you all.

156
00:07:31,084 --> 00:07:34,621
But moving forward, I ask
for those who had faith in me

157
00:07:34,655 --> 00:07:36,557
to support
a different candidate,

158
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:38,459
and I strongly believe
that cheadle

159
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:40,461
is the right person for the job.

160
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:45,399
The zodiacs are not a monolith,
but that does not mean

161
00:07:45,432 --> 00:07:48,802
there are none among us
who share similar goals,

162
00:07:48,836 --> 00:07:51,672
and my own goals
are all shared by cheadle.

163
00:07:51,705 --> 00:07:55,509
The association must now choose
the right path,

164
00:07:55,542 --> 00:07:59,012
and she, with her balanced
sensibility, can lead us!

165
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,726
Piyon: And now let’s move on

166
00:08:12,759 --> 00:08:15,495
to speeches from
the four remaining candidates.

167
00:08:15,529 --> 00:08:17,798
There’s one thing
we’d like you to note.

168
00:08:17,831 --> 00:08:20,767
The work we’re doing here
is really important,

169
00:08:20,801 --> 00:08:23,470
so everyone who’s gathered
inside the hall today

170
00:08:23,504 --> 00:08:25,206
will be asked
to stay in the building

171
00:08:25,239 --> 00:08:28,609
until the 13th chairman
has been selected!

172
00:08:28,642 --> 00:08:30,944
( Crowd murmuring, grumbling )

173
00:08:33,046 --> 00:08:34,948
Pariston: Huh.

174
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:40,020
( Leorio grumbles )

175
00:08:40,053 --> 00:08:41,955
♪

176
00:08:51,265 --> 00:08:52,933
Amane: Is anyone inside?

177
00:08:52,966 --> 00:08:55,168
Butler: Just tsubone and canary.

178
00:08:58,272 --> 00:09:00,174
♪

179
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:20,160
Amane: How’s master alluka?

180
00:09:20,194 --> 00:09:21,829
Killua: She’s still asleep.

181
00:09:21,862 --> 00:09:23,797
I’ll wait ’til she wakes up.

182
00:09:30,704 --> 00:09:31,872
Almost there.

183
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:34,508
Just a little longer, gon.

184
00:09:37,611 --> 00:09:39,913
- ( Monitor beeping )
- ( Ventilator hissing )

185
00:10:00,601 --> 00:10:01,869
♪

186
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:07,507
Piyon: It’s possible we’ll
continue to have multiple ties,

187
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:09,910
but we’ve arranged
to have all necessary provisions

188
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:12,112
here on site, so rest easy!

189
00:10:12,145 --> 00:10:14,447
There’s nothing stopping us
from repeating the vote

190
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:18,051
as many times as necessary,
whether it takes hours or days.

191
00:10:18,085 --> 00:10:19,820
I’ll say it one more time.

192
00:10:19,853 --> 00:10:22,789
You will not be permitted
to leave the hall

193
00:10:22,823 --> 00:10:26,026
until the 13th chairman
has been selected.

194
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:28,628
Okay, now that
that’s cleared up,

195
00:10:28,662 --> 00:10:30,030
let’s move on to a speech

196
00:10:30,063 --> 00:10:33,099
from the candidate
in fourth place, mizaistom.

197
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:37,037
Ging: This is bad.

198
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:39,039
♪

199
00:10:39,072 --> 00:10:41,841
mizaistom:
To eliminate pariston,

200
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:44,478
I will sacrifice myself.

201
00:10:45,546 --> 00:10:46,914
I’ll be very brief.

202
00:10:46,947 --> 00:10:49,249
Of the four candidates onstage,

203
00:10:49,283 --> 00:10:51,852
only one of us
is truly qualified,

204
00:10:51,885 --> 00:10:54,654
and that candidate is cheadle.

205
00:10:54,688 --> 00:10:56,089
( Crowd murmuring )

206
00:10:56,123 --> 00:10:57,658
Mizaistom: Please understand

207
00:10:57,691 --> 00:10:59,826
i’m not saying
I don’t want to be chairman.

208
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,495
It’s just not my time.

209
00:11:01,528 --> 00:11:05,032
first, I want to train
and mentor the hunters under me

210
00:11:05,065 --> 00:11:06,800
and focus all of my efforts

211
00:11:06,834 --> 00:11:08,903
on becoming
a triple star hunter.

212
00:11:10,571 --> 00:11:13,941
i would appreciate it
if you would respect my wishes

213
00:11:13,974 --> 00:11:15,909
and help end
this election today.

214
00:11:17,077 --> 00:11:18,979
That’s all.

215
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,814
Leorio: Hmm.

216
00:11:20,848 --> 00:11:22,583
What should I say?

217
00:11:22,616 --> 00:11:23,917
Piyon: Next, we have

218
00:11:23,951 --> 00:11:26,120
the candidate
currently in third place.

219
00:11:26,153 --> 00:11:30,024
miss cheadle,
the floor is all yours.

220
00:11:30,057 --> 00:11:32,726
cheadle: I’ll try
to keep this quick, everyone.

221
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:36,229
Ladies and gentlemen,
after much consideration,

222
00:11:36,263 --> 00:11:41,301
I believe our next chairman
should be leorio.

223
00:11:41,335 --> 00:11:42,903
( Crowd murmuring )

224
00:11:42,936 --> 00:11:44,237
Cheadle: That is all.

225
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:48,809
mizaistom:
She can’t be serious.

226
00:11:48,842 --> 00:11:51,111
What is cheadle thinking?

227
00:11:51,144 --> 00:11:54,714
leorio: No way am I
gonna be the next chairman.

228
00:11:54,748 --> 00:11:56,717
Hell, I didn’t even want
to be elected.

229
00:11:56,750 --> 00:12:00,053
but I guess
I should say what I want.

230
00:12:00,087 --> 00:12:02,823
my mind isn’t
on this election, anyway.

231
00:12:02,856 --> 00:12:06,293
piyon: Okay.
Thank you very much!

232
00:12:06,326 --> 00:12:09,095
Next, we have the candidate
in second place.

233
00:12:09,129 --> 00:12:11,598
Mr. Leorio, you’re up!

234
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,936
Cheadle: Where’d that smile
of yours go, pariston?

235
00:12:15,969 --> 00:12:19,172
if you think i’ll
just let you have it your way,

236
00:12:19,206 --> 00:12:20,741
you’re mistaken.

237
00:12:20,774 --> 00:12:24,645
piyon: Hello?
It’s your turn to speak now.

238
00:12:24,678 --> 00:12:27,748
Is something wrong, Mr. Leorio?

239
00:12:27,781 --> 00:12:30,317
Mr. Leorio?

240
00:12:31,385 --> 00:12:33,354
Don’t ignore me, damn it!

241
00:12:33,387 --> 00:12:38,058
if you’re asleep,
I am so gonna strangle you!

242
00:12:38,091 --> 00:12:39,125
Leorio: Hmm.

243
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:41,762
Eh? Who, me?

244
00:12:41,795 --> 00:12:43,730
♪

245
00:12:45,766 --> 00:12:46,767
( Thinking )
Nothing.

246
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,169
I’m drawing a complete blank.

247
00:12:49,203 --> 00:12:51,706
What am I even doing up here?

248
00:12:53,073 --> 00:12:56,310
In that case, to hell with it.

249
00:12:58,011 --> 00:13:02,916
Fine. Guess i’ll just say
what’s on my mind.

250
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:06,086
If i’m elected chairman,
i promise...

251
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,188
I will abuse my authority!

252
00:13:08,222 --> 00:13:11,392
( Crowd gasping )

253
00:13:11,425 --> 00:13:14,395
As my very first
order of business,

254
00:13:14,428 --> 00:13:18,732
i’ll command all of you to do
something to help save gon!

255
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:27,308
The truth is, this isn’t
where I should be right now.

256
00:13:27,341 --> 00:13:30,845
Well, as much as i’d like to,

257
00:13:30,878 --> 00:13:34,048
it’s not like I could help gon
if I were with him, anyway

258
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:38,418
gon is a friend, a buddy,

259
00:13:38,452 --> 00:13:42,957
and right now, while i’m
here with you, he’s dying.

260
00:13:44,458 --> 00:13:48,228
I just recently
realized it, though.

261
00:13:48,262 --> 00:13:51,232
While I was off studying,

262
00:13:51,265 --> 00:13:54,235
not thinking
of anyone but myself,

263
00:13:54,268 --> 00:13:57,938
drinking,
moving from place to place,

264
00:13:57,971 --> 00:14:01,141
wanking off,
partying with girls,

265
00:14:01,175 --> 00:14:03,277
surfing the net...

266
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:07,848
He was putting
his life on the line,

267
00:14:07,881 --> 00:14:09,816
fighting to save others.

268
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,985
he was part
of the chairman’s team.

269
00:14:13,387 --> 00:14:16,457
And now, even as we speak,

270
00:14:16,490 --> 00:14:20,461
one of them is risking
his own life to save gon’s.

271
00:14:20,494 --> 00:14:26,300
I wish there was more I could
have done besides talk to him,

272
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:29,369
but that was all I could do
to help my friend.

273
00:14:29,403 --> 00:14:32,473
So if I become chairman,

274
00:14:32,506 --> 00:14:36,010
i promise
I won’t stop talking to you.

275
00:14:37,511 --> 00:14:40,781
Please help save gon!

276
00:14:40,814 --> 00:14:42,049
Use your heads!

277
00:14:42,082 --> 00:14:44,418
If you have an idea, do it!

278
00:14:45,953 --> 00:14:48,255
tell me how
I can save him, please!

279
00:14:48,288 --> 00:14:49,823
I’ll do it!

280
00:14:54,795 --> 00:14:57,831
Cheadle: Ging,
I think I understand

281
00:14:57,865 --> 00:14:59,834
why you didn’t dodge
when he punched you.

282
00:15:01,335 --> 00:15:03,070
Even in that moment,

283
00:15:03,103 --> 00:15:06,206
you already knew
he might have a chance to win.

284
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:08,409
( No audible dialogue )

285
00:15:10,811 --> 00:15:14,081
i’m perfectly fine
with having him as chairman.

286
00:15:14,114 --> 00:15:15,983
Leorio: Damn.

287
00:15:16,016 --> 00:15:19,253
Sorry. Think I said
more than I needed to.

288
00:15:19,286 --> 00:15:23,023
Forget the wanking part.
i’m done.

289
00:15:26,827 --> 00:15:28,796
( Applause )

290
00:15:28,829 --> 00:15:30,798
Cheadle: If we’re there
to support him,

291
00:15:30,831 --> 00:15:34,201
i’m sure he’ll make
a good chairman,

292
00:15:34,234 --> 00:15:37,137
very good, indeed.

293
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:45,111
Piyon: Finally, we have
the candidate in first place.

294
00:15:45,145 --> 00:15:47,914
You’re up, Mr. Pariston.

295
00:15:47,948 --> 00:15:50,317
Please be quiet, everyone!

296
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:53,954
Cheadle: It’s over, pariston.

297
00:15:53,987 --> 00:15:56,456
Say what you want.
It doesn’t matter.

298
00:15:56,490 --> 00:16:01,528
My 87 votes, mizai’s 72 votes,
and the 57 independent votes

299
00:16:01,562 --> 00:16:04,231
will be added to leorio’s 95.

300
00:16:04,264 --> 00:16:06,032
No question.

301
00:16:06,066 --> 00:16:07,134
( Crowd murmuring )

302
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:09,202
cheadle:
That gives him 311 votes,

303
00:16:09,236 --> 00:16:12,339
which means he’ll have over 50%.

304
00:16:12,372 --> 00:16:16,343
The 13th chairman
will be leorio.

305
00:16:16,376 --> 00:16:19,546
Piyon: I’m gonna have to ask you
to quiet down now, everyone!

306
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:22,883
And refrain from using
your mobile phones!

307
00:16:24,318 --> 00:16:25,920
In a minute,

308
00:16:25,953 --> 00:16:28,389
things are going to get loud
in here, so be warned!

309
00:16:31,391 --> 00:16:34,895
Pariston: Everyone, feel free
to keep using your cell phones.

310
00:16:34,928 --> 00:16:37,864
That’s the true hunter spirit.
Am I right, folks?

311
00:16:37,898 --> 00:16:39,967
When this is over, I promise

312
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,570
i’ll do all I can
to assist gon’s full recovery.

313
00:16:43,604 --> 00:16:46,607
that being said,
we have to keep such matters

314
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:49,276
separate
from the election at hand.

315
00:16:49,309 --> 00:16:52,979
Only one candidate
is qualified to lead us,

316
00:16:53,013 --> 00:16:55,182
and that’s Mr. Mizaistom!

317
00:16:55,215 --> 00:16:57,417
( Crowd gasping )

318
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:02,923
You see, i’ve learned something
after serving

319
00:17:02,956 --> 00:17:06,026
as chairman netero’s
vice chairman for three years.

320
00:17:06,059 --> 00:17:09,396
There are three conditions
vital for a chairman to meet.

321
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:11,998
First is combat strength!

322
00:17:12,032 --> 00:17:16,236
That is, given the nature
of what we do, quite necessary,

323
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:18,606
as evidenced
by the recent events.

324
00:17:18,639 --> 00:17:21,208
Second is experience!

325
00:17:21,241 --> 00:17:24,444
Wisdom is much enhanced
by experience.

326
00:17:24,478 --> 00:17:27,915
As a hunter, of course you can
never have too much of it.

327
00:17:27,948 --> 00:17:29,917
Cheadle: Why?

328
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:33,086
Every time he opens his mouth,

329
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:35,522
I get so incredibly irritated.

330
00:17:35,556 --> 00:17:39,060
Pariston: And the third
is having what it takes!

331
00:17:39,092 --> 00:17:42,028
Cheadle: I know why. It must be.

332
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:44,331
That I can sense
he’s never saying

333
00:17:44,364 --> 00:17:46,233
what he’s truly thinking.

334
00:17:46,266 --> 00:17:48,001
pariston:
We all want to make sure

335
00:17:48,035 --> 00:17:50,337
that the association
is in good hands,

336
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:51,972
but there aren’t
very many people

337
00:17:52,005 --> 00:17:54,274
that we could all agree
would make great leaders.

338
00:17:54,308 --> 00:17:56,911
Cheadle’s lacking combat,

339
00:17:56,944 --> 00:17:58,646
and leorio is inexperienced.

340
00:17:58,679 --> 00:18:01,549
Cheadle: Stop.
Do not get emotional.

341
00:18:01,582 --> 00:18:05,252
Pariston: As for myself,
I lack all three!

342
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:07,954
you were supposed
to laugh there, but okay.

343
00:18:07,988 --> 00:18:12,626
Cheadle: He is after something.
I need to figure out what it is.

344
00:18:12,659 --> 00:18:16,363
Pariston: But only one of us
has all three, and that person,

345
00:18:16,396 --> 00:18:19,566
in my professional opinion,
is Mr. Mizaistom.

346
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:22,970
Cheadle: Pariston has 290 votes.

347
00:18:23,003 --> 00:18:27,174
Of those, 120 are
from the temp hunters.

348
00:18:27,207 --> 00:18:30,177
30 come from the personal
and administrative staff

349
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:32,713
of the departments he heads.
No surprise there.

350
00:18:32,746 --> 00:18:34,615
♪

351
00:18:34,648 --> 00:18:38,318
It doesn’t matter what he says.
They get their own commands

352
00:18:38,352 --> 00:18:40,921
straight from the rat himself,
as it were.

353
00:18:42,422 --> 00:18:44,090
Piyon: Okay, moving on.

354
00:18:44,124 --> 00:18:47,494
It’s time for the q-and-a
session with the candidates.

355
00:18:47,528 --> 00:18:49,363
Cheadle: Pariston’s speech

356
00:18:49,396 --> 00:18:51,999
will create a split
among the independents,

357
00:18:52,032 --> 00:18:54,735
who were all most likely
leaning toward leorio.

358
00:18:54,768 --> 00:18:56,336
That’ll probably look like...

359
00:18:58,438 --> 00:19:01,441
But that would just push
the election out another round,

360
00:19:01,475 --> 00:19:04,144
which matches our goal.

361
00:19:05,479 --> 00:19:06,714
Unless...

362
00:19:06,747 --> 00:19:09,216
Will something change
during the q-and-a?

363
00:19:09,249 --> 00:19:12,619
( Ging snoring )

364
00:19:12,653 --> 00:19:14,421
♪

365
00:19:14,454 --> 00:19:17,223
cheadle: Fine.
I’ll figure this out myself.

366
00:19:17,257 --> 00:19:20,060
pariston: Well,
you mind if I go first?

367
00:19:20,093 --> 00:19:22,128
Mizaistom: No, i’ll go first.

368
00:19:22,162 --> 00:19:26,600
Like I mentioned here earlier,
I don’t want to be the chairman.

369
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:28,602
pariston: Actually
you made it a point to say

370
00:19:28,635 --> 00:19:30,704
that it’s not that you
don’t want to be chairman.

371
00:19:30,737 --> 00:19:34,174
However, this isn’t about
what you want, now, is it?

372
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:35,342
Mizaistom: Huh?

373
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,710
pariston:
The only thing that matters

374
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:38,478
is how the voters feel.

375
00:19:38,512 --> 00:19:41,482
Sometimes a job can only
be done by a certain person.

376
00:19:41,515 --> 00:19:42,616
That’s what it means

377
00:19:42,649 --> 00:19:44,718
to "have what it takes,"
as you said.

378
00:19:44,751 --> 00:19:46,620
- Mizaistom: Huh?
- Pariston: That is why

379
00:19:46,653 --> 00:19:48,755
you shouldn’t be talking
about how you feel.

380
00:19:48,789 --> 00:19:50,357
No more tricks.

381
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:53,293
Let’s leave everything
to the people’s will.

382
00:19:53,327 --> 00:19:55,362
Both: This guy’s
got some nerve!

383
00:19:55,395 --> 00:19:59,199
Cheadle: But why
is he pushing mizai?

384
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:01,469
What does he expect us
to do now?

385
00:20:01,502 --> 00:20:03,137
let greed
get the better of us

386
00:20:03,170 --> 00:20:05,773
and allow mizai
to drop to second place?

387
00:20:05,806 --> 00:20:07,041
♪

388
00:20:07,074 --> 00:20:08,576
That’ll never happen,

389
00:20:08,609 --> 00:20:11,779
because the votes for leorio
are basically undecided.

390
00:20:11,812 --> 00:20:15,616
If leorio loses, they’re likely
to swing to pariston

391
00:20:15,649 --> 00:20:17,417
as their next choice,

392
00:20:17,451 --> 00:20:19,486
but, if leorio
stays in the running,

393
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:21,589
the votes
previously cast for myself

394
00:20:21,622 --> 00:20:24,091
and the openly
anti-pariston mizai

395
00:20:24,124 --> 00:20:26,193
will definitely go to leorio.

396
00:20:26,226 --> 00:20:29,796
he’ll hold on
to teradein’s anti-zodiac votes,

397
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:32,733
and the morel votes
are also anti-pariston.

398
00:20:32,766 --> 00:20:35,469
They won’t vote for him,
no matter what.

399
00:20:37,137 --> 00:20:39,106
You got that, mizai?

400
00:20:39,139 --> 00:20:41,575
mizaistom: Yeah.
I read you loud and clear.

401
00:20:41,608 --> 00:20:43,710
Defeating pariston
is the ultimate goal.

402
00:20:45,546 --> 00:20:49,116
I trust my instincts
as a crime hunter.

403
00:20:49,149 --> 00:20:50,617
There’s no proof,

404
00:20:50,651 --> 00:20:54,221
and it’s entirely possible
that his hands are clean.

405
00:20:54,254 --> 00:20:58,592
However, he clearly lives
in the shadows.

406
00:20:58,625 --> 00:21:00,260
One thing is certain.

407
00:21:00,294 --> 00:21:03,531
We can’t let him rule
the association any longer.

408
00:21:03,564 --> 00:21:06,634
It’s obvious that,
try as he might,

409
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:09,336
not even chairman netero
could rein him in.

410
00:21:11,171 --> 00:21:14,241
This election has one purpose.

411
00:21:14,274 --> 00:21:17,410
cheadle: This is where
we’ll destroy pariston’s regime.

412
00:21:17,444 --> 00:21:19,846
♪

413
00:21:21,715 --> 00:21:24,384
narrator: And so
the eighth round of voting

414
00:21:24,418 --> 00:21:27,254
for the 13th chairman begins.

415
00:21:31,358 --> 00:21:33,660
(♪ Singing in Japanese )

416
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:35,660
